Widows


Executive Vice President Karen Altfest recently spoke with the Wall Street Journal to discuss the specialized financial services in place at Altfest Personal Wealth Management for women and widows.




 Read more on how Altfest Personal Wealth Management meets the needs of widows. The media often seeks Karen out for her expertise in widowhood planning::


 
Karen Altfest was interviewed for the article  "Survivors' Biggest Mistake: Widows and Widowers Often Lose Money Needlessly; the IRA Rollover Penalty" 
 Karen Altfest was featured in the article and video,  "Alone...and Confused: Widows often need special financial advice" 
 Karen Altfest was featured in the WSJ Voices blog article  "Karen Altfest, on Working With Widows" 
 

 Karen Altfest is featured in  "Widows Aren't Your Grandmother" 



 Karen Altfest authored the cover story,  "Surviving a Loss: Smart Steps for Coping With Widowhood" 

For more information, please call Karen Altfest at 212-406-0850.






