						TimesSquare Capital Management LLC Has $4.91 Million Stake in Allergan PLC. (NYSE:AGN)					

						 July 23rd, 2017  - 0 comments - Filed Under -
 by Latisha Jones 


							Filed Under: Finance - SEC Filing Articles 







Tweet










TimesSquare Capital Management LLC lowered its stake in  Allergan PLC. (NYSE:AGN) by 4.9% during the first quarter, according to its most recent 13F filing with the SEC. The institutional investor  owned 20,564 shares of the company’s stock after selling 1,050 shares during the period. TimesSquare Capital Management LLC’s holdings in Allergan PLC. were worth $4,913,000 at the end of the most recent quarter. 
Other large investors have also recently added to or reduced their stakes in the company. Ibex Wealth Advisors purchased a new stake in  Allergan PLC. during the fourth quarter valued at about $538,000.  Becker Capital Management Inc. bought a new position in shares of  Allergan PLC. during the fourth quarter valued at $23,304,000.  Auxier Asset Management raised its position in shares of  Allergan PLC. by 16.1% in the fourth quarter. Auxier Asset Management now owns 7,840 shares of the company’s stock valued at $1,646,000 after buying an additional 1,090 shares during the last quarter.  Kentucky Retirement Systems bought a new position in shares of  Allergan PLC. during the fourth quarter valued at $5,716,000.  Finally, Kentucky Retirement Systems Insurance Trust Fund bought a new position in shares of  Allergan PLC. during the fourth quarter valued at $2,550,000. 84.53% of the stock is currently owned by institutional investors. 
Shares of Allergan PLC. (NYSE:AGN) opened at 250.97 on Friday. Allergan PLC. has a 12 month low of $184.50 and a 12 month high of $261.27. The firm has a 50-day moving average of $239.66 and a 200 day moving average of $234.93. The firm has a market cap of $84.29 billion, a P/E ratio of 7.82 and a beta of 1.16. 




Allergan PLC. (NYSE:AGN) last posted its earnings results on Tuesday, May 9th. The company reported $3.35 earnings per share for the quarter, topping the Thomson Reuters’ consensus estimate of $3.32 by $0.03. Allergan PLC. had a return on equity of 7.29% and a net margin of 82.42%. The firm had revenue of $3.57 billion during the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $3.53 billion. During the same period in the previous year, the company earned $3.04 EPS. The company’s revenue for the quarter was up 5.1% on a year-over-year basis.  On average, equities research analysts anticipate that  Allergan PLC. will post $16.08 EPS for the current fiscal year. 
TRADEMARK VIOLATION WARNING: “TimesSquare Capital Management LLC Has $4.91 Million Stake in Allergan PLC. (NYSE:AGN)” was first  published by Daily Political and is the property of of Daily Political. If you are accessing this article on another domain, it was illegally copied and republished in violation of United States & international copyright and trademark legislation. The correct version of this article can be read at https://www.dailypolitical.com/2017/07/23/timessquare-capital-management-llc-has-4-91-million-stake-in-allergan-plc-nyseagn.html. 
Several brokerages have recently weighed in on AGN. Credit Suisse Group  reiterated an “outperform” rating and set a $286.00 price objective (up from $274.00) on shares of Allergan PLC. in a report on Thursday. Deutsche Bank AG  reiterated a “buy” rating and set a $273.00 price objective (up from $265.00) on shares of Allergan PLC. in a report on Monday, July 17th. Royal Bank Of Canada  set a $284.00 price objective on shares of Allergan PLC. and gave the stock a “buy” rating in a report on Sunday, July 16th. Piper Jaffray Companies  reiterated a “hold” rating and set a $231.00 price objective on shares of Allergan PLC. in a report on Friday, July 14th. Finally, Zacks Investment Research upgraded shares of Allergan PLC. from a “hold” rating to a “buy” rating and set a $270.00 price objective on the stock in a report on Tuesday, July 11th. Seven analysts have rated the stock with a hold rating and fifteen have given a buy rating to the stock. The stock currently has a consensus rating of “Buy” and a consensus target price of $273.78.
In related news, Director Nesli Basgoz sold 1,889 shares of the business’s stock in a transaction that occurred on Thursday, May 18th. The stock was sold at an average price of $220.45, for a total value of $416,430.05. The transaction was disclosed in a document filed with the Securities & Exchange Commission, which can be accessed through the SEC website. 0.36% of the stock is currently owned by insiders. 
About Allergan PLC.
Allergan, Inc is a multi-specialty healthcare company. The Company focuses on developing and commercializing pharmaceuticals, biologics, medical devices and over-the-counter (OTC) products. It discovers, develops and commercializes a range of products for the ophthalmic, neurological, medical aesthetics, medical dermatology, breast aesthetics, urological and other specialty markets.
