        11/7/2015
    

My wife and I have been clients of Altfest Personal Wealth Management for over 25 years. This firm has always put our financial health as their first priority. They have protected us and managed to preserve our retirement savings through the dot com and deep recession eras. When other advisers were being pressured by their clients to get them into dot com stocks, Altfests saw to it that we did not get into these risky investments.  Likewise, they had us hold tight in the recession and bought stocks when the market was very low.  Suffice it to say we have fared extremely well now that we are in our retirement years.We have a well diversified portfolio that includes stocks, mutual funds, real estate funds, real estate and oil partnerships and municipal bonds. Also, it is important to note that they carefully balance your mutual fund investments so there is minimal overlap in investment sectors and minimum costs and fees for each fund.The best thing about the Alfests is that they take a personal interest in each of their clients.  We are friends with a number of other clients who share this same experience.As far as access is concerned, we have always found the firm ready to answer our questions and meet with us at a moments notice.On a personal note, the Alfests are the most ethical people we have ever met.  They are also very philanthropic. Karen Altfest has received numerous awards for her charitable work including as one of the founders of the New York Pantry for the poor. They have also set up scholarship funds at Pace University and City College.We recommend them with enthusiasm!!!




        Was this review …?
    







